{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e76a68fa-0927-4268-b88e-7149af6b7463","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 3.x → 4.x dropped the VSTest bridge by default.**\n\nStarting with MSTest.Sdk 4.0, projects use **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** as the sole runner and no longer ship the VSTest adapter/bridge. That's why `vstest.console` can't discover your tests — the DLL no longer contains the VSTest-compatible entry points it expects.\n\n### You have two options\n\n**Option 1 – Switch your CI to the native runner (recommended):**\n```bash\n# Run the test project directly instead of vstest.console\ndotnet run --project TestProject.csproj -- --list-tests   # discover\ndotnet run --project TestProject.csproj                    # execute\n# or simply:\ndotnet test TestProject.csproj\n```\n`dotnet test` in recent SDK versions auto-detects Microsoft.Testing.Platform projects.\n\n**Option 2 – Re-enable the VSTest bridge:**\nAdd this to your `.csproj`:\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>false</EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>\n</PropertyGroup>\n<ItemGroup>\n  <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.VSTestBridge\" />\n</ItemGroup>\n```\n\nOption 1 is the intended path forward — MSTest.Sdk 4.x is designed to run without VSTest.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"74001ecb-b2a7-45fb-94aa-73d07e36427c","outputTokens":341,"requestId":"1BCD:AAEEE:C0092C:D93B94:6A03F322"},"id":"c6b9d8d2-f8f6-4e09-b70f-2ed6c9d79499","timestamp":"2026-05-13T03:42:35.756Z","parentId":"984ce2d4-8dd2-409b-a24d-b4498049597a"}
